title: 820-3115 (A1278) - No PPVCORE_S0_CPU
message: Board starts, nothing on screen. Fans goes high, U5410 corroded. Will replace that soon, but it's only for sensor, right?

title: 820-3115 (A1278) - No PPVCORE_S0_CPU
message: High fan is caused by temperature sensor issue, from my experience. If U5410 is for sensor it could be.

title: 820-3115 (A1278) - No PPVCORE_S0_CPU
message: R7402/3 checked? Any liquid near U7400?

title: 820-3115 (A1278) - No PPVCORE_S0_CPU
message:
"Board starts, nothing on screen."
Post CPU voltage; you should detect a drop from 1.15V to 0.8V aprox.
Test for USB activity.

Solve corrosion around U5410 and check SMC_OTHER_HI_ISENSE.

title: 820-3115 (A1278) - No PPVCORE_S0_CPU
message:
U5410 replaced. Fan is okay now.

There was corrosion around U7400. A couple of things were replaced/jumped. 

Computer starts, but in safe mode. Hm?

title: 820-3115 (A1278) - No PPVCORE_S0_CPU
message:
If only starts in SMC bypass, there is still some sensor error.
Check the output for all sensors on page 50.
